# Events by Jordyn — Design System

**Stack:** Next.js (App Router) + TypeScript + Tailwind. Static export (`output: 'export'`, `images.unoptimized: true`). Deploy target: Cloudflare Pages (free tier, commercial use allowed). Do NOT use Vercel's free Hobby plan — it's non-commercial only.

**Visual source of truth:** @events-by-jordyn-homepage-mockup.html — match it closely, porting its CSS into Tailwind + reusable React components.
**Full content/structure spec:** @events-by-jordyn-build-spec.md

**Aesthetic:** elegant, editorial, airy. Pink is a restrained accent — white space and photography dominate. Never make it look "cute" or templated.

**Colors (add to Tailwind theme):** white `#FFFFFF`, cream `#FAF6F4`, blush `#E8BCC3`, rose `#B76E79` (primary action), rose-dark `#9E5A65` (hover), charcoal `#2E2E30` (text), slate `#7A7A80` (muted), line `#EAE6E3` (borders).

**Fonts (next/font/google):** Playfair Display (headings), Jost (body). Uppercase letter-spaced eyebrow labels above section headings.

**Always:** mobile-first, responsive, accessible (semantic HTML, alt text, visible focus states, honor `prefers-reduced-motion`). Componentize and keep files small. Placeholder images get a `{/* TODO: replace with real photo */}` comment. Build ONE spec slice per task — don't scaffold everything at once.
